* Plans the work on development of the functional software security in accordance with the tasks of the employer;
* Managing a team of product managers, distributing their tasks, monitoring their performance and efficiency
* Recruiting new employees for the team, conducting interviews and assessing competencies
* Personnel planning for the team, planning hiring and workload
* Distributes tasks between the different teams and supervises the implementation of the software development work in accordance with the specifics of each project;
* Represents the interests of software users in the team in which they works;
* Develops specific requirements for the software security;
* Conducts an analysis and compares the technical and functional characteristics of the software with products competing with those of the employer and uses this analysis in planning the work on the development of the software products;
* Макеs strategic planning of the main stages of development and setting goals in connection with the development of the software in the employer's enterprise;
* Advises other programmers on technical and functional characteristics in relation to the software they are developing;
* Collaborate with other members of development teams on complex multi-development implementations (provisioning, integration, billing, etc.);
* Collaborate with other teams on application issue resolution, product functionality, design clarification, infrastructure support, quality assurance.
* Lead a product focused on simplifying the end-to-end experience of creating and managing WordPress websites.
* Contribute to long-term product vision and strategy for WordPress products.
* Align product strategy to company objectives and target key results.
* Partner with the engineering team and other product managers across teams to translate product strategy into initiatives, epics, and executable stories.
* Keep current on the competitive WordPress landscape and user needs, conduct competitive analysis, and lead innovation in owned product.
* Work across WebPros with Engineering, Product Marketing, Product UX, Sales, Support, and other departments to ensure the overall success of the product.
* Participating in the hiring process and interviewing Product Manager candidates. Goal setting and annual performance reviews for team members.
* Cross-team collaboration to improve the product and identify improvements.

**About Us**
 Komodo Consulting is a technology and strategy firm specializing in Digital Transformation. Operating in Portugal and Poland, we provide IT Consulting & Nearshore services. We support both public and private sector organizations through two main areas:




* Consulting — with a focus on strategy, investment analysis, and digital process improvement;
* IT Team Augmentation — helping clients scale and strengthen their tech teams.


**The project**
 We are seeking a Lead Data Engineer to work on a tech project.




**You will have the following responsibilities:**
* Lead the design and implementation of scalable data platforms and pipelines aligned with the client’s AI-driven roadmap;
* Own the end-to-end architecture of the data warehouse and Medallion layers (Bronze, Silver, Gold), ensuring robustness and maintainability;
* Drive the adoption of best practices in SQL development, performance optimization, and data modeling across the team;
* Collaborate closely with business and technical stakeholders to translate requirements into reliable, cloud-native data solutions;
* Ensure data quality, governance, and documentation from ingestion to consumption, enabling trustworthy analytics and AI use cases;
* Mentor and support other data engineers, fostering a culture of continuous improvement and experimentation with modern data technologies.


**You need to have the following skills/experience:**
* More than 5 years of professional experience as a Data Engineer or in similar data-focused roles;
* Advanced SQL expertise, including T-SQL and/or PL-SQL, with strong skills in querying, programming, and performance tuning;
* Specialist-level knowledge in at least one major cloud data platform such as Microsoft Azure (Synapse, SQL Database, Fabric), AWS or Snowflake;
* Hands-on experience building BI and reporting solutions using tools such as Power BI, Qlik or Tableau;
* Practical experience with Data Warehouse Automation (DWA) and modern data architecture patterns such as the Medallion architecture (Bronze, Silver, Gold);
* Strong data quality mindset, ensuring reliability, consistency and governance of data from ingestion onwards;
* Interest in exploring and adopting new technologies (for example Fabric, vector databases or AI integration) to address evolving client needs;
* Availability and willingness to work on-site in Sweden;
* Full professional fluency in English and Portuguese.


**Location**
 Onsite - Stockholm, Sweden.
